'''Human replica droids''', or '''HRDs''', were sophisticated [[Synthskin/Legends|synthskin]] and [[biofiber]]-covered [[Droid/Legends|droids]] designed to be nearly indistinguishable from [[Human/Legends|Humans]]. Their design was similar enough to Human anatomy that even high-quality medical scanners were not always able to identify them as inorganic, although they were able to discern some differences from the typical Human. They were sometimes referred to as "'''meatdroids'''" or "'''droid clones'''". Unlike true [[Cloning/Legends|clones]], a droid clone could be created in under three months. HRDs were programmed to think that they were real humans, even having fabricated childhood memories.

==History==
HRD experiments included [[Project Decoy]], a plot by the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]] to create Rebel-controlled [[Human/Legends|Human]] replica droids used to replace [[Imperial officer/Legends|Imperial officers]]. Unfortunately for the Alliance, it lacked the necessary funding to continue the project. However, the Alliance did make at least one HRD, a [[Tardi (droid)|replica]] of [[Viscount (title)/Legends|Viscount]] [[Tardi]].

[[File:Human_replica_droid_TofG.jpg|thumb|left|200px|A damaged HRD under fire.]]

The [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire]], however, managed to perfect HRD technology during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]] when it hired designers [[Massad Thrumble]] and [[Simonelle]] the [[Ingoian]], who had stolen the technology from Confederate Holdouts and databases. They produced a Human replica droid named [[Guri]], later purchased as an [[Assassin/Legends|assassin]] by [[Prince/Legends|Prince]] [[Xizor/Legends|Xizor]] of [[Black Sun/Legends|Black Sun]] for nine million [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]]. Following this success, Simonelle relocated to the [[Minos Cluster/Legends|Minos Cluster]], establishing his own HRD [[Simonelle's workshop|workshop]], while Thrumble remained in Imperial service, [[Lexhannen Torlock (droid)|creating]] [[Frija Torlock (droid)|replicas]] of [[Governor/Legends|Governor]] [[Lexhannen Torlock]] of [[Corulag/Legends|Corulag]], and his daughter, [[Frija Torlock|Frija]]. These droids' self-awareness was so advanced that they ultimately rejected their programming as decoys, and fled to [[Hoth/Legends|Hoth]] to start a new life.

Following the [[Death/Legends|death]] of Xizor [[Battle over Coruscant|over]] [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]], Guri sought out her creator, Thrumble, and asked for her memory to be purged of her assassination programming. The procedure, carried out on [[Hurd's Moon]], was a success, and Guri became a fully self-governing droid.

Approximately [[5 ABY/Legends|one year]] after the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]], the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] completed Project Decoy, though its HRDs proved to be clumsy and inferior to Thrumble's designs. Project Decoy HRDs saw action in only a few missions, including one in which a [[Leia Organa II|duplicate]] of [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] helped kill the would-be [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Trioculus]].

During the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]], [[Stanton Rendar|Dash Rendar]] set up an operation in the Minos Cluster to transfer the life-essence of paying customers into HRD bodies. He used the [[entechment]] technology pioneered by the [[Ssi-ruu|Ssi-Ruuk]], hoping that the procedure held the secret to eternal life.

